<Layout title='Terms of Service — ADHD Flow Lab'>
  <article class='post'>
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class='post-date'>Last updated: July 2026</p>
    <div class='post-content'>
      <p>By using ADHD Flow Lab (adhd-blog-kappa.vercel.app) and our related content channels, you agree to these terms.</p>
      <h2>Use of Content</h2>
      <p>Our articles, newsletters, and digital products are provided for personal use. Content is for informational purposes and is not medical advice.</p>
      <h2>Digital Products</h2>
      <p>Digital products (such as printable planners) are sold via Etsy and are subject to Etsy's terms. Because they are instant downloads, all sales are final.</p>
      <h2>Third-Party Platforms</h2>
      <p>We publish content to and integrate with third-party platforms including YouTube, TikTok, Pinterest, Instagram, beehiiv, and Etsy. Your use of those platforms is governed by their respective terms.</p>
      <h2>Affiliate Links</h2>
      <p>Some links are affiliate links; we may earn a commission at no extra cost to you.</p>
      <h2>Automated Content Posting</h2>
      <p>We operate automated tools that publish short-form video clips to social platforms — including through the TikTok Content Posting API — but only to accounts whose owner has explicitly connected and authorized them through the platform's official OAuth consent flow. We post only to those authorized accounts, request the minimum permissions required, and never post to accounts that have not granted permission. You can revoke access at any time in your platform's app settings.</p>
      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>We may update these terms at any time. Continued use constitutes acceptance.</p>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Questions? Reach out via our newsletter reply or channel contact options.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
